<dl id="n12023b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12023b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12023b"> 23(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> S. Patrick learns Ir history / from old hag</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">On raconte que <mark>Saint Patrice, voulant conna&icirc;tre l&apos;histoire de l&apos;Irlande, alla consulter une bonne vieille</mark> qui avait vu passer plusieurs g&eacute;n&eacute;rations humaines <br><font color="green">[It is said that when Saint Patrick wanted to learn the history of Ireland, he consulted an old hag who had seen many human generations come and go]</font> <small> [TLMM]Th&eacute;odore-Claude Hersart, Vicomte de La Villemarqu&eacute;, <cite a>Myrdhinn, ou l'enchanteur Merlin</cite></a> (1862) IX</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12005h" href="c12all.htm#c12005h">VI.C.12:005(h)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
